source.14d636f7: According to the graph of result, in December 2020, the third outbreak point of COVID-19  occurred in South Korea, and the number of new patients in a single day continued to surge for several days.　South Korea's health care system is collapsing because of the shortage of hospital beds and a surge in new cases and seriously cases.South Korea's capital area densely populated, the rapid spread of the covid-19 caused that the non-capital area also rebounded.The outbreak mainly occurred in family or acquaintance gatherings, community centers, markets, restaurants and other places of daily life. These places have a large population flow, and it is difficult for the Covid-19 prevention bureau to trace the source of infection. The proportion of patients infected by unknown routes once again exceeded 20%.If the route of infection cannot be mastered in time, it is difficult to trace close contacts for epidemiological investigation, and the possibility of missing the "hidden source of infection" is greater.This leads to the occurrence of "N transmissions", which lead to more patients.At the same time, there have been days of infections outside South Korea's capital circle, making it harder for the authorities to respond.So far, 14 people have been confirmed at a community center in Chungnam's county and 15 at a car factory in North county.South Korea's health system is already overloaded with beds, with nearly two-thirds of the new cases confirmed on Dec 7th being "pending."As the Covid-19 gradually severe, serious lack of hospital beds, Seoul finally decided to set up a temporary "container ward".
source.11882d29: Because nighttime services have also been hard hit by the outbreak's rebound, it took the government a lot of effort just to track down close contacts in previous Seoul nightclub outbreaks. Therefore, from January 10, the government will require anyone entering nightclubs and karaoke facilities to show a QR code (a type of QR code) that can read personal information to track the infection status of each person in real time.The tracking model has already been implemented in parts of Seoul.People only need to provide their mobile phone number, which does not reveal any other personal information.The information will be deleted automatically after four weeks in a government database, according to the Ministry of Health.

source.cd74e165: South Korea and Italy are the most severely affected countries in the world after March 2020, among which South Korea is the hardest hit country in Asia. The country first detected cases on February 16, and the outbreak officially started on February 19, and became difficult to control on February 20.As we can see from the graph, there was a big jump in the number of confirmed people in March 2020.I checked the relevant information and learned that the main reason for the outbreak was the gathering of religious groups and the lack of protection measures.South Koreans are addicted to believe in a variety of religions. If you come to South Korea, you will encounter large and small churches, it can be said that in addition to the convenience store is the church most. Due to the mass gathering of ten thousand cults in South Korea and no protective measures in advance, the first outbreak of the new coronavirus occurred in South Korea. Before, South Korea did a good job in controlling the Covid-19, but it was not expected that the outbreak would be caused by cults.It is mainly caused by the Shinchonji Church , which has a roll call system, where everyone has to hold a special card to swipe it, and any absence is recorded and followed up. Its culture is that even if you are sick, you still have to come on Sunday.If you're too sick to make it on Sunday, make sure you come on Monday or Tuesday to make up the time.All personnel shall not wear anything, including glasses on their faces during prayer.Even after the outbreak of Covid-19, people were still banned from wearing masks.They say wearing masks is disrespectful to god. In addition, another 40 people from a religious group in the southern city of Chengnan were confirmed on Mar.15 and Mar.16, and there were many other incidents of religious gatherings that were not reported as a major issue.In addition, the number of confirmed cases is also increasing due to the collective infection in the Daegu Hansalom Sanatorium Hospital.On March 10, a cluster of COVID-19 infections occurred at the Korea Building in Sundolyeong-dong, Kuro-gu District, Seoul. 64 people were confirmed to be infected, and testing for the remaining people is still underway.The first confirmed patient in the building was an employee who worked at the insurance company's call center on the 11th floor of the building. The patient was diagnosed with COVID-19 on Monday, and a number of other employees and family members were subsequently diagnosed with COVID-19 during the lockdown of the building and the home quarantine of close contacts.Due to the large number of people infected by cluster transmission and the fact that the confirmed patients live in a dispersed area and travel in a large radius, the cluster event has aroused great concern in South Korea.The series of infections led to an outbreak in South Korea in March.But thanks to the proper control of the South Korean government, the Covid-19 was under control.
source.9754afdf: ##### Information and discussion from the results and news
source.8c9ba1ed: The South Korean government's approach in many aspects is problematic. At the beginning of the COVID-19 outbreak, South Korea controlled it well and the Covid-19 did not spread to a large extent.But the South Korean government became complacent after some achievements, and the Covid-19 began to spread rapidly, coinciding with the holiday, when the number of South Korean travel out of control.By the time the government tried to urge people not to travel, it was too late, the Covid-19 had begun to spread rapidly, and people's awareness of the Covid-19 had declined
source.ba0d7165: South Korea has lowered its Covid-19 prevention level for two weeks since February 15, continuing to ban gatherings of more than five people.South Korea's Central Bureau of Epidemiological Prevention and Countermeasures on February 13 released the "social distance restriction measures" adjustment program.According to the plan, restrictions on business hours at 480,000 facilities in the capital circle, including classes and cinemas, and 520,000 non-capital circle restaurants, cafes and indoor sports facilities will be lifted.The closing time of restaurants, cafes, indoor sports facilities, singing rooms, party rooms and other public gathering facilities in the Capital Circle will also be extended from 9 p.m. to 10 p.m.According to the South Korean government's current Covid-19 prevention secondary response standard, five types of entertainment facilities are prohibited from operating. However, considering the livelihood difficulties of individual businesses, the government allows entertainment facilities across the country to operate until 10 PM in compliance with the epidemic prevention code.However, local governments can adjust their level of prevention according to the situation of the Covid-19. I hope  Covid-19 can be brought under control as soon as possible.

source.0e2ac922: According to the graph of result, the second outbreak point was around August 2020. I checked relevant information and found that a number of religious cluster infections broke out again in South Korea, and the Covid-19 rebounded sharply. The number of new cases in a single day for four consecutive days exceeded 100 on the from 14th to 17th. On August 15, during the National Rehabilitation Day in South Korea, some religious groups held illegal rallies in defiance of the government's executive order to ban them, causing a large number of people to gather and causing panic among anti-epidemic authorities.In response, South Korean President issued a strong condemnation on 16th, saying that it is a challenge to the national epidemic prevention system, and a serious threat to the lives of citizens.South Korea has seen a rebound in the Covid-19 situation because the "Love First" church and other outbreaks of cluster infection, until 16th, associated with the church has reached 249 confirmed cases.This is the third largest cluster of infections in South Korea, after 5,214 cases at the Shinchonji Church and 277 cases at the Itaewon nightclub in Seoul.In addition, the collective infection in the army has also become one of the causes that cannot be ignored.
source.2ec6bf89: There is also the issue of religion. Most churches have switched to online worship since the outbreak, but more than 80 churches across the country are still not following the guidelines and will be warned, said by head of the epidemic prevention department at the Central Emergency Management Department.During a meeting on COVID-19 prevention and control, the Prime Minister of South Korea said that some churches that do not comply with the prevention and control regulations will be severely punished in accordance with the law, including closing churches and imposing fines.He said the actions of individual religious groups were not only reckless, but also harmful to the entire community.
source.6ca82c6e: According to the graph of result, then, in February 2021, South Korea started vaccinating, and there was an initial upward trend as health care workers and others started to get their first doses, but the numbers were not large.Since then, vaccination numbers have declined, and there has been a general backlash from the public over reports of side effects and deaths in the news.After that, through the continuous efforts of the government and the continuous upgrading of vaccines, the Korean people recognized the safety of vaccines and the increase in the number of vaccines. As a result, the government liberalized the vaccination policy, leading to a sharp increase in the vaccination rate, which reached the peak in May 2021.We hope the Covid-19 will be effectively controlled in the future.
